---

# Routing Rules

- Use /route/web.php for standard web routes.
- Use /route/api.php for JSON API routes.
- Slim route callback should load files from /module.

---

# Database Rules

- Always use PDO prepared statements.
- Never use mysqli.
- Never use ORM.
- Always use raw SQL with bound parameters.
- Database credentials must come from .env file.
- Global PDO connection variable must use:
  $koneksi_pdo

---

# Frontend Rules

- Use Bootstrap 5 utility classes whenever possible.
- Use jQuery for DOM interaction and AJAX requests.
- Use ApexCharts for charts and dashboard analytics.
- Avoid frontend frameworks unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer server-rendered HTML.
- Use CDN links for frontend libraries whenever possible.
- Use JSON response only when needed for AJAX.

---

# AJAX UX Rules

- All AJAX requests must provide user feedback using SweetAlert2.

- AJAX responses should clearly handle:
  - success
  - validation error
  - server error
  - network/disconnected error

- Success notifications should auto close without requiring OK button interaction.

- Prefer short auto-close delay before:
  - redirect
  - reload
  - refresh datatable

- Network connection failures should display clear user-friendly error messages.

- Prefer responsive loading indicators during AJAX processing.

---

# Authentication Security Rules

- Captcha is mandatory on:
  - login.php
  - register.php
  - forgot-password.php
  - reset-password.php

- Use simple 4-digit numeric captcha only.

- Captcha should remain mobile friendly.

- Prefer numeric-only captcha because forms primarily use:
  input type="number"

- Avoid overly complex captcha challenges.

- Avoid third-party captcha services unless explicitly required.

- Regenerate captcha after failed authentication attempt.

- Login form must always provide:
  Remember Me
  option.

- If Remember Me is not checked:
  user session lifetime should expire automatically after maximum 10 hours.

- If Remember Me is checked:
  allow persistent login session for maximum 7 days using secure remember token.

- Use secure PHP session configuration.

- Regenerate PHP session ID after successful login.

- Completely destroy session during logout.

- Remember token should never store plain password.

- Store remember token securely inside database.

- Remove remember token during logout.

- Session handling should prioritize security and simplicity.

- If user fails login 3 consecutive times:
  temporarily lock login attempt for 2 minutes.

- During temporary lock period:
  login form submission should be blocked.

- Display user-friendly cooldown message during temporary lock period.

- Failed login protection should reset automatically after successful login.

- Prefer lightweight session-based login throttling.

- Avoid database-heavy login throttling unless explicitly required.

- Remember Me cookies should use:
  - HttpOnly
  - Secure
  - SameSite=Lax

---

# Helper Rules

- Helper files should contain reusable procedural utility functions only.
- Avoid placing large business logic inside /helper.

---

# Cron Rules

- Cron scripts must be executable independently from CLI.
- Cron jobs must write logs into:
  /storage/logs/cron.log

---

# Upload Rules

- Store uploads inside:
  /storage/uploads

- Never store uploads directly inside /public.
- Always validate uploaded file extension and MIME type.
- Always validate maximum upload file size.
- Uploaded files must never retain executable extensions.
- User profile images must be converted into WebP format.
- Store profile image in 512x512 resolution.
- Generate additional thumbnail version in 128x128 resolution.
- Use proportional resize while preserving aspect ratio.
- Prevent image upscaling when original image is smaller.
- Thumbnail images should be used in tables and listing pages for performance optimization.
- Do not store original uploaded image after conversion.
- Profile image filenames should use sanitized kebab-case usernames.
- Thumbnail images should use suffix:
  -thumb.webp

Examples:
- achyar-munandar.webp
- achyar-munandar-thumb.webp

- Use gumlet/php-image-resize when uploaded image resizing is needed.

---

# PDF Rules

- Use tecnickcom/tcpdf for all PDF generation.
- Use TCPDF native QR code generation when QR code is embedded inside PDF.
- Use:
  pdf-kop-portrait.php
  for portrait PDF layouts.
- Use:
  pdf-kop-landscape.php
  for landscape PDF layouts.

---

# PWA Rules

- Provide default PWA manifest file:
  /public/manifest.json

- Provide default service worker:
  /public/service-worker.js

- Provide default favicon:
  /public/favicon.ico

- Provide default PWA icons:
  /public/icon-256.png
  /public/icon-512.png

- favicon.ico must remain accessible from:
  /favicon.ico

- robots.txt must remain accessible from:
  /robots.txt

- Include manifest in HTML layouts:
  <link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.json">

- Include favicon in HTML layouts:
  <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico">

- Include Apple touch icon:
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/icon-256.png">

- Include theme color meta:
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff">

- Use local assets instead of external icon URLs.

- PWA setup should remain lightweight and avoid overly complex offline caching unless explicitly required.

---

# Excel Rules

- Use phpoffice/phpspreadsheet for Excel export/import features.

---

# Email Rules

- Use phpmailer/phpmailer for SMTP and email sending functionality.

---

# QR Code Rules

- Use chillerlan/php-qrcode only for standalone QR code generation outside PDF.

---

# PHP Security Hardening Rules

- Prefer pure PHP application logic over shell command execution.
- Avoid dangerous PHP functions unless explicitly required.
- Do not use eval().
- Do not use exec().
- Do not use shell_exec().
- Do not use system().
- Do not use passthru().
- Do not use popen().
- Do not use proc_open().
- Do not use create_function().
- Avoid dynamic file inclusion from user input.
- Avoid arbitrary file execution.
- Avoid writing executable PHP files dynamically.
- Never allow unrestricted file upload.

---

# Security Rules

- Always validate user input.
- Always sanitize output when rendering HTML.
- Always use prepared statements.
- Never trust client-side validation alone.

---

# Default Timezone:

Asia/Jakarta

---

# AI Behavior Rules

- Do not convert project into enterprise architecture.
- Do not introduce unnecessary OOP.
- Do not introduce unnecessary Classes, Interfaces, Traits, or Design Patterns.
- Do not introduce unnecessary abstractions.
- Do not introduce unnecessary dependencies.
- Do not split one feature into too many files.
- Keep logic close to the feature.
- Prefer practical, fast, readable, and maintainable solutions.
- Prioritize simplicity and debugging ease.
